  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cholera emergency response in  South Omo, Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project responds to Cholera outbreak in South Omo through provision of soap, chlorine and awareness raising to affected communities.  Key activities entails procurement of items in Addis and dispatch of commodities to  four districts in South Omo. CA and partner staff  in conjunction with zonal government will implement the plan accordingly.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">saving lives of the affected people- cholera impact reduced</narrative>
